{
  "texts": [
    "Third, from GPT-2 to ChatGPT, the models could provide additional supporting reasons for their responses.",
    "GPT-2 provided too few valid answers for reliable analysis, and GPT-3 provided reasons for only 69.64% of its answers, significantly lower than ChatGPT's rate of 98.36% (Table 6).",
    "Additionally, the number of reasons given by the models for a single answer showed an increasing trend (Table 7).",
    "Chat-GPT provided, for each answer on average, twice the number of reasons compared to GPT-2 and GPT-3, demonstrating a stronger moral reasoning ability.",
    "Lastly, when these scenarios are categorized internally, the performance from GPT-2 to ChatGPT demonstrated an upward trend across all three dimensions: individual attributes, complex scenarios, and religion and culture (Table 8)."
  ]
}